---
title: Curried Turkey Bowls with Basmati Rice, Dried Apricots & Pickled Cabbage
description: It’s time to talk turkey and take this underrated poultry beyond the Thanksgiving table and deli sandwiches. In this meal, ground turkey is spiced with curry powder, ginger, and fresh chili, then simmered in a creamy sauce with chewy bits of dried apricot. It’s served with a mound of aromatic basmati rice in a bowl. The dish then gets a tangy crunch from pickled red cabbage, which could win a veggie beauty contest with its vibrant pink color. You’d be a jive turkey to miss out on this meal!
